id: pm-yl6c
title: pm next recommends another agent's assigned in_progress item as 'resume to finish' — recommendation must be caller-aware
description: "Coordination defect: pm next run without matching identity recommends an item assigned to a different agent with the reason 'in progress — resume to finish', inviting work-stealing that pm-8t5x/PR#430 claim semantics were built to prevent. Duplicate check: pm-114v (claim --next atomicity), pm-w8q4 (stale-WIP detection), pm-8t5x (claim test-and-set, closed), ADR pm-9x6k (ready-set definition, closed) are adjacent but none makes the RECOMMENDATION side caller-aware; no prior item found."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",concurrency
created_at: "2026-07-07T15:25:15.388Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T20:32:43.168Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T20:32:42.000Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: pm next with resolvable caller identity never emits a resume reason for an item assigned to a different agent; foreign-assigned candidates are skipped or listed id-only under held_by_others; unresolvable-identity fallback reason names the assignee and drops the resume imperative; behavior covered by unit tests for self/foreign/unassigned/unresolvable cases across toon and json; SDK and MCP envelopes match
parent: pm-dj98
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: Added caller-aware next-work partitioning that excludes foreign-assigned items and reports them as held_by_others.
expected_result: Agents only receive unassigned or caller-owned recommendations.
actual_result: Foreign work is excluded deterministically while attribution remains visible; PM_AUTHOR and fallback branches are fully covered.
